### Variable Definition
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/job-postings

### 1. Create a Job Posting
# This mimics the JobPostingRequest DTO
# @name createJob
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Lead Java Developer",
  "company": "Tekmetric",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "location": "Houston, TX",
  "remote": true,
  "jobType": "FULL_TIME",
  "experienceLevel": "SENIOR",
  "salaryMin": 140000,
  "salaryMax": 180000,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Building the future of auto repair software.",
  "requirements": "Java 21, Spring Boot 4",
  "benefits": "Generous PTO, Health, 401k",
  "expiresAt": "2026-12-31T23:59:59"
}

### Capture the ID from the previous response
@createdId = {{createJob.response.body.id}}

### 2. Get the Created Job by ID
# Uses the dynamic ID from the create step
GET {{baseUrl}}/{{createdId}}

### 3. Filter Jobs (Search)
# Demonstrates the JobPostingFilter logic
GET {{baseUrl}}?location=houston&remote=true&page=0&size=5

### 4. Update the Job
# Demonstrates the update logic and guard checks
PUT {{baseUrl}}/{{createdId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Lead Platform Engineer",
  "company": "Tekmetric",
  "department": "Platform",
  "location": "Remote",
  "remote": true,
  "jobType": "FULL_TIME",
  "experienceLevel": "EXECUTIVE",
  "salaryMin": 160000,
  "salaryMax": 200000,
  "currency": "USD",
  "description": "Updated description",
  "requirements": "Updated requirements",
  "benefits": "Unlimited PTO",
  "expiresAt": "2026-12-31T23:59:59"
}

### 5. Delete the Job
# Final cleanup in the demo
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/{{createdId}}